<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id74a60020-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s153901"><num value="153901">§ 153901.</num><heading> Organization</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The National Yeomen (F) (in this chapter, the “corporation”) is a body corporate and politic in the District of Columbia.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id74a60021-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7">(<ref href="/us/pl/105/225">Pub. L. 105–225</ref>, <date date="1998-08-12">Aug. 12, 1998</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/112/1431">112 Stat. 1431</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/113/237/s3/c/8/B">Pub. L. 113–237, § 3(c)(8)(B)</ref>, <date date="2014-12-18">Dec. 18, 2014</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/128/2840">128 Stat. 2840</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
